        <type>int</type>
        <definition>static int XSecure_SetSlrIndex</definition>
        <argsstring>(XSecure_ClientInstance *InstancePtr, u32 SlrIndex)</argsstring>
        <name>XSecure_SetSlrIndex</name>
        <param>
          <type>XSecure_ClientInstance *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>SlrIndex</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sets slr index in the Secure client instance. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to XSecure_ClientInstance </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>SlrIndex</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Slr index to be set in instance</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS - On valid input SlrIndex.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE - On invalid SlrIndex.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is applicable to only Versal </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Validate SlrIndex and assign it to instance pointer </para>        </inbodydescription>
